        WHAT_IS_IT_2                                                          = 13535,  -- What is it?
        SIR_WE_TOO_ARE_PREOCCUPIED_HERE_AT_THE                                = 13536,  -- Sir, we too are preoccupied here at the capital with the rebuilding of fortifications and rallying of the troops. In anticipation of your orders we attempted to garner what forces we could to send into the field, but... I'm afraid such a force would be significantly lacking in its capabilities to reinforce the location, sir.
        YOU_NEEDN_T_WORRY_YOURSELF_ABOUT_THAT_I                               = 13537,  -- You needn't worry yourself about that. I had considered our lack of manpower and took the liberty of scouting a formidable ally to our cause.
        A_FORMIDABLE_ALLY_SIR                                                 = 13538,  -- A formidable ally, sir?
        I_HAD_HEARD_THE_KINGDOM_WATH_LOW_ON                                   = 13539,  -- I had heard the Kingdom wath low on infantry, but I hadn't imagined the thituathion wath thith dire.
        AH_THERE_YOU_ARE_MR_MAYAKOV_YOUR_ASSISTANCE                           = 13540,  -- Ah, there you are, Mr. Mayakov. Your assistance is most welcome!
        WHAT_YOU_SEE_IS_QUITE_REMARKABLE_IN_ITS                               = 13541,  -- What you see is quite remarkable in its own right, considering the blow which we suffered at the Battle of La Theine.
        SIR_RAGELISE_IF_I_MAY_INQUIRE_AS_TO                                   = 13542,  -- Sir Ragelise, if I may inquire as to who our guest is?
        OF_COURSE_THIS_IS_THE_LEADER_OF_THE                                   = 13543,  -- Of course. This is the leader of the prestigious Troupe Mayakov. He has agreed to lend us the strength of his dancers in our desperate hour.
        TROUPE_MAYAKOV_THE_D_DANCERS_SIR                                      = 13544,  -- Troupe Mayakov? The d-dancers, sir?
        DON_T_BE_MISTAKEN_KNIGHT_THE_DANCERS_MAY                              = 13545,  -- Don't be mistaken, knight. The dancers may hide themselves away in obscurity in these traveling troupes...
        BUT_THEY_SHALL_PLAY_A_KEY_ROLE_ON                                     = 13546,  -- But they shall play a key role on the battlefields in our opposition to this damnable Beastman Confederate!
        BUT_SURELY                                                            = 13547,  -- But surely...
        THE_MAJORITY_OF_TROUPE_MAYAKOV_TH_MEMBERTH_ARE                        = 13548,  -- The majority of Troupe Mayakov'th memberth are orphanth who were brought up at the convent in La Vaule.
        BELIEVE_ME_WHEN_I_TELL_YOU_THAT_NONE                                  = 13549,  -- Believe me when I tell you that none are more dithheartened than we by the current thtate of affairth there.
        WE_MAY_NOT_BE_THE_IMPOTHING_FIGHTING_FORTHE                           = 13550,  -- We may not be the impothing fighting forthe that you were hoping for, but we will do everything in our power to protect our homeland.
        PORTIA                                                                = 13551,  -- Portia!
        THE_LOVELY_LADY_YOU_THEE_BEFORE_YOU_ITH                               = 13552,  -- The lovely lady you thee before you ith not only one of our more talented performerth, but altho our motht accomplithed battle danther. No doubt Portia here will prove an invaluable addition to your cauthe.
        ARE_YOU_SURE_YOU_ARE_UP_TO_THE                                        = 13553,  -- Are you sure you are up to the task, my lady?
        BY_YOUR_WILL_MILORD_SHOULD_IT_PLEASE_YOU                              = 13554,  -- By your will, milord. Should it please you, Sir Ragelise, I would willingly follow you to the very ends of Vana'diel.
        WHAT_ABOUT_THE_OTHER_ONE_THE_CUTE_ONE                                 = 13555,  -- What about the other one? The cute one... Lilisette, I think her name was. Can she come along as well?
        BAH_LILITHETTE_ITH_THTILL_BUT_A_MERE_CHILD                            = 13556,  -- Bah! Lilithette ith thtill but a mere child. Only rethently hath the joined our troupe and I have no intenthionth of endangering her life.
        SIGH_ALL_RIGHT                                                        = 13557,  -- <Sigh>... All right...
        IT_IS_SETTLED_THEN_WE_DEPART_AT_ONCE                                  = 13558,  -- It is settled, then. We depart at once! Knights, bid farewell to your ladies.
        GULP_F_FAREWELL_SIR                                                   = 13559,  -- <Gulp>... F-farewell, sir?
        DO_NOT_BE_SO_EASILY_SHAKEN_BOYS_IT                                    = 13560,  -- Do not be so easily shaken, boys! It is only a figure of speech! Tell them naught but you love them, and shall hold them in your arms again before many nights pass!
        DISMISSED_3                                                           = 13561,  -- Dismissed!
        THE_DOOR_IS_FIRMLY_LOCKED                                             = 13562,  -- The door is firmly locked...
        I_WONDER_IF_PERHAPS_NO_IT_COULDN_T                                    = 13563,  -- I wonder if perhaps... No, it couldn't be...
        WH_MY_APOLOGIES_SIR_MA_AM_YOU_GAVE                                    = 13564,  -- Wh--!? My apologies, sir/ma'am]. You gave me a bit of a start, is all.
        I_BEG_YOUR_INDULGENCE_MY_MIND_WANDERS_AND                             = 13565,  -- I beg your indulgence. My mind wanders and is ill at ease. If you would please be so kind as to excuse me.
        UNLESS_IF_I_MAY_BE_SO_BOLD_AS                                         = 13566,  -- Unless... If I may be so bold as to impose upon you, sir/ma'am]. A certain dilemma of sorts has been plaguing me for quite some time now. It has me up at nights, truth be told.
        DOES_THIS_TALK_INTEREST_YOU_IMMENSELY_YES_NOT                         = 13567,  -- Does this talk interest you? Immensely, yes. Not in the least, no.
        VERY_WELL_I_WOULD_HUMBLY_ASK_THAT_YOU                                 = 13568,  -- Very well. I would humbly ask that you leave me to my own devices, then. I bid you good day, sir/ma'am].
        THAT_COULD_ONLY_MEAN                                                  = 13569,  -- That could only mean...
        NO_NO_BY_ALTANA_THAT_SIMPLY_CANNOT_BE                                 = 13570,  -- No, no. By Altana, that simply cannot be...
        AH_BUT_FIRST_DO_ALLOW_ME_TO_INTRODUCE                                 = 13571,  -- Ah, but first, do allow me to introduce myself. My name is Nichais, the humble and most junior of sons born to a countryside lord of no notable circumstance.
        I_MADE_THE_JOURNEY_TO_THE_CAPITAL_HERE                                = 13572,  -- I made the journey to the capital here with hopes of studying under the most prestigious historians in the Kingdom. I have been fortunate enough to secure such a post, interning at the private residence of a very well-known scholar.
        AND_MAY_I_ASK_YOUR_NAME_KIND_ADVENTURER                               = 13573,  -- And may I ask your name, kind adventurer?
        IT_IS_BOTH_AN_HONOR_AND_A_PRIVILEGE                                   = 13574,  -- It is both an honor and a privilege to make your acquaintance, %.
        WELL_I_SHALL_NOT_PRESUME_TO_WASTE_ANY                                 = 13575,  -- Well, I shall not presume to waste any more of your time than I absolutely must. Tell me, does the topic of the great wyrms interest you? For it is they I wish to speak to you about this day!
        PRAY_TELL_HAVE_YOU_HEARD_THE_LEGENDS_OF                               = 13576,  -- Pray tell, have you heard the legends of the so-called Eastdrake? It is believed the beast resides somewhere in the craggy, cavernous expanses of Grauberg, though any such accounts are of course no more than hearsay.
        THE_LEGEND_ITSELF_HAS_BEEN_PASSED_DOWN_FOR                            = 13577,  -- The legend itself has been passed down for hundreds of years now. The oldest existing literature on the subject claims that the wyrm's ancestral home lies somewhere in the Far East.
        MANY_FINER_DETAILS_OF_THE_STORIES_DIFFER_FROM                         = 13578,  -- Many finer details of the stories differ from one another, but one astonishing fact seems to be agreed upon by all the sources I have had the chance to study. They say that the wyrm relished in taking on the form of an elegant young Elvaan maiden, under the guise of which she would call upon villages and hamlets.
        UNTIL_ONE_DAY_SHE_CAPRICIOUSLY_TOOK_WING_AND                          = 13579,  -- Until one day she capriciously took wing and bore the high winds to our continent of Quon, settling in the harsh environs of Grauberg. There she met a great and mighty warrior, and they bound themselves to their words and to each other, entering into a noble and timeless oath.
        A_PACT_BORN_OF_HONOR_AND_SWEARING_PROTECTION                          = 13580,  -- A pact born of honor, and swearing protection. The Eastdrake thus became the Mountain's Eye, vowing to give her life in defense of the peak, the warrior, and his line, for all of time.
        I_HAVE_SINCE_BEEN_TO_GRAUBERG_TO_BEAR                                 = 13581,  -- I have since been to Grauberg to bear witness for myself. The only vestiges now left of this ancient tradition are the scattered Elvaan settlements which still hold true to the cult of the great wyrm.
        EVEN_SO_THE_MERE_THOUGHT_OF_A_WYRM                                    = 13582,  -- Even so, the mere thought of a wyrm what takes on the shape of an Elvaan maiden... Surely the stuff of fairy tales. Until now, most all of the pundits here in the capital who occupy themselves with the study of such topics, myself included, had simply written the entire account off as a mummer's farce. Or at the very best, an anachronistic myth.
        BUT_SOMETHING_HAS_HAPPENED_RECENTLY_WHICH_HAS_GIVEN                   = 13583,  -- But something has happened recently which has given me cause to reconsider my views.
        SOLDIERS_OF_OUR_OWN_ALLIED_FORCES_RETURNING_FROM                      = 13584,  -- Soldiers of our own Allied Forces returning from campaigns in Grauberg bring back most intriguing tales! Eyewitness accounts of an enormous dragon in the region!
        UPON_HEARING_THIS_MY_THOUGHTS_WENT_IMMEDIATELY_TO                     = 13585,  -- Upon hearing this, my thoughts went immediately to the legend of the Mountain's Eye, and my hope of proving the myth was rekindled.
        AND_SO_WE_COME_TO_MY_PRESENT_DILEMMA                                  = 13586,  -- And so we come to my present dilemma. Please forgive the brevity of my synopsis, but you must admit it is a rather intriguing story, yes?
        I_CANNOT_HELP_BUT_WONDER_WHETHER_OR_NOT                               = 13587,  -- I cannot help but wonder whether or not there is some way of confirming if this wyrm actually exists. And if so, could it truly be the Mountain's Eye of which the legends speak? The wyrm who walks as an Elvaan, as the books say?
        I_IMPLORE_YOU_IF_YOUR_TRAVELS_EVER_HAPPEN                             = 13588,  -- I implore you, if your travels ever happen to take you within the vicinity of Grauberg, would you mind investigating the premises for me?
        I_WOULD_FOREVER_BE_IN_YOUR_DEBT                                       = 13589,  -- I would forever be in your debt, %.
        HOW_VERY_GOOD_TO_SEE_YOU_AGAIN                                        = 13590,  -- %! How very good to see you again!
        I_TRULY_HOPE_YOU_CAN_FORGIVE_MY_ABRUPT                                = 13591,  -- I truly hope you can forgive my abrupt parting back in Grauberg. But it was not without good reason that I felt the need to return to the city's walls at once, I promise you.
        IT_CONCERNS_THE_WYRM_WE_SAW_TAKING_FLIGHT                             = 13592,  -- It concerns the wyrm we saw taking flight, and the young girl those hooded callers were referring to as Areuhat.
        I_GATHER_THAT_YOUR_POWERS_OF_REASON_ARE                               = 13593,  -- I gather that your powers of reason are sound enough to reach the obvious conclusion.
        YES_I_CAN_NOW_STATE_WITHOUT_THE_SLIGHTEST                             = 13594,  -- Yes, I can now state without the slightest doubt that the creature we saw was indeed the Mountain's Eye of Grauberg! And the young Elvaan maiden named Areuhat, none other than the same wyrm in its mortal guise!
        ACCORDING_TO_THE_RECORDED_LEGENDS_WHICH_I_HAVE                        = 13595,  -- According to the recorded legends which I have been poring over...
        HER_SUPPLICANTS_HAD_DUBBED_HER_ODZMANOUK_WHICH_FOR                    = 13596,  -- Her supplicants had dubbed her Odzmanouk, which for whatever reason she found to be too harsh for her liking. Instead, she insisted that her followers refer to her as Areuhat, and Areuhat alone, and so it was.
        ALL_OF_THE_SIGNS_I_TOOK_NOTE_OF                                       = 13597,  -- All of the signs I took note of back in Grauberg I have confirmed here in the annals. The angel-like hair with its platinum brilliance, the ornate eastern fineries and garments, the manner of speech. And that unmistakable Elvaan maiden...
        I_CONCEDE_IT_IS_A_BIT_MUCH_TO                                         = 13598,  -- I concede it is a bit much to absorb all at once, and perhaps difficult to believe. But as you well saw for yourself, the splendor that being possessed was nothing short of a bona fide deity. Never before have I witnessed such radiance, nor felt such presence.
        THE_GRACE_WITH_WHICH_HER_WINGS_EMBRACED_THE                           = 13599,  -- The grace with which her wings embraced the sky, and the solemn, divine aura about her. The books had not prepared me, they made no mention of this...this sublime majesty.
        STILL_EVEN_IF_THAT_YOUNG_ELVAAN_SHOULD_PROVE                          = 13600,  -- Still, even if that young Elvaan should prove to be the Eastdrake, it is no cause to rejoice.
        THE_MEN_ACCOMPANYING_HER_APPEARED_TO_ME_TO                            = 13601,  -- The men accompanying her appeared to me to be emissaries dispatched from the east, seeking her audience. I cannot be sure of their motives, but no doubt they are seizing upon this opportunity while Grauberg is racked by the maelstrom of war.
        IT_SOUNDED_AS_THOUGH_THEY_WERE_ATTEMPTING_TO                          = 13602,  -- It sounded as though they were attempting to persuade the Mountain's Eye to relinquish her post and return to the East. And from the looks of it, she was not entirely opposed to the idea. I fear we haven't much time!
        TO_THINK_I_HAVE_COME_THIS_FAR_ONLY                                    = 13603,  -- To think I have come this far, only to lose sight of my goal now! But no, I must not give myself to despair just yet.
        THERE_MAY_STILL_BE_A_CHANCE_TO_REMEDY                                 = 13604,  -- There may still be a chance to remedy the situation.
        COUNTLESS_HOURS_SPENT_IN_THE_CATHEDRAL_S_LIBRARIES                    = 13605,  -- Countless hours spent in the cathedral's libraries laboring over the archives have not gone unrewarded. I uncovered a mere whisper of a clue, lost to the ages beneath stacks of papyrus and parchment.
        IT_WOULD_SEEM_THAT_KEEPING_THE_PEACE_AROUND                           = 13606,  -- It would seem that keeping the peace around Grauberg was not the only charge put to the Elvaan warrior by the Mountain's Eye in their pact with one another.
        THERE_IS_MENTION_OF_A_CERTAIN_FANCY_OF                                = 13607,  -- There is mention of a certain fancy of Areuhat's, which was agreed to be given to her as an offering on a daily basis.
        THE_TEXT_I_DISCOVERED_HOWEVER_WAS_EXTREMELY_CRYPTIC                   = 13608,  -- The text I discovered, however, was extremely cryptic. A riddle, one might say... Do listen.
        IT_READ_AN_AGELESS_ARMOR_IMPENETRABLE_AND_YET                         = 13609,  -- It read, An ageless armor, impenetrable, and yet of no metal wrought. To lay at rest only the comfort of anvil-hard beds are sought. Protected from without, protecting from within, yielding naught.
        UNFORTUNATELY_IT_DOES_NOT_GO_ON_TO_SPECIFY                            = 13610,  -- Unfortunately, it does not go on to specify exactly what the offering is. No doubt it was intended to be a closely-guarded secret known only to a select few. I'm afraid these were the only details I was able to uncover.
        BUT_IF_WE_WERE_SOMEHOW_ABLE_TO_ASCERTAIN                              = 13611,  -- But if we were somehow able to ascertain the true identity of this item, perhaps we could make an offering of it in the manner that the text describes. And if that young Elvaan maid is truly the great wyrm of the East...
        I_AM_THE_FIRST_TO_ADMIT_THAT_IS                                       = 13612,  -- I am the first to admit, that is a great many if's. But should they all prove true, by the grace of the Goddess... Well, then perhaps ingratiating ourselves with the great Eastdrake of legend is not as unrealistic as I thought!
        YOU_MUST_FORGIVE_MY_PERSISTENT_IMPOSITIONS_IT_WAS                     = 13613,  -- %, you must forgive my persistent impositions. It was truly never my intention to come to rely so heavily upon you. But I fear I have another task to ask of you.
        I_PLAN_TO_REMAIN_HERE_AND_THROW_MYSELF                                = 13614,  -- I plan to remain here and throw myself wholeheartedly into the deciphering of this riddle. If you happen across anything in your travels that you feel may fit this description, would you be so good as to bring it to me?
        I_PROMISE_THAT_YOUR_EFFORTS_WILL_NOT_GO                               = 13615,  -- I promise that your efforts will not go unrewarded!
        YOU_VE_RETURNED_SO_GOOD_OF_YOU_TO                                     = 13616,  -- %, you've returned! So good of you to come again. Pray tell, were you able to gain any insight into our little puzzle?
        HMMM_I_CERTAINLY_HAD_NOT_THOUGHT_OF_THIS                              = 13617,  -- Hmmm... I certainly had not thought of this. Though, to be honest, I'm not sure I see the relevance. Perhaps we are veering farther from the truth.
        WHAT_S_THIS_HMMM_MOST_INTRIGUING_I_DARE                               = 13618,  -- %, what's this? Hmmm... Most intriguing. I dare say, I think you may be on to something with this.
        YES_IT_JUST_MAY_BE_BUT                                                = 13619,  -- Yes, it just may be... But...
        ALAS_I_FEAR_THIS_MAY_BE_A_BIT                                         = 13620,  -- Alas, %, I fear this may be a bit too large.
        BY_THE_GODDESS_AN_AUTHENTIC_HOW_DID_YOU                               = 13621,  -- By the Goddess! An authentic %! How did you happen across a copy of this!? Are you aware of the value and rarity of this text, %?
        I_CONFESS_THE_THOUGHT_HAD_OCCURRED_TO_ME                              = 13622,  -- I confess, the thought had occurred to me as well. But on reflection, I realized an ancient tome such as this would never make for a practical daily offering. Though unfortunately not the item we are searching for, please, keep it with you. And keep it safe.
        HM_WHAT_S_THIS_THEN                                                   = 13623,  -- Hm? What's this, then?
        WHY_OF_ALL_THINGS_WHATEVER_COULD_HAVE_POSSESSED                       = 13624,  -- Why, %, of all things, whatever could have possessed you to bring me this? But, if only... No, it couldn't possibly... Could it?
        AN_AGELESS_ARMOR_IMPENETRABLE_AND_YET_OF_NO                           = 13625,  -- An ageless armor, impenetrable, and yet of no metal wrought. Well, I suppose that is one way of stating it. The shell bug certainly is armored.
        TO_LAY_AT_REST_ONLY_THE_COMFORT_OF                                    = 13626,  -- To lay at rest only the comfort of anvil-hard beds are sought. Protected from without, protecting from within, yielding naught.
        I_VE_HEARD_IT_SAID_THAT_THE_SHELL                                     = 13627,  -- I've heard it said that the shell bug is a parasite which thrives within the shells of Quadav! They derive safety from within while at the same time ridding their hosts of other disease-ridden vermin. Textbook symbiosis, really.
        IT_COULD_BE_THAT_THE_ANVIL_HARD_BEDS                                  = 13628,  -- It could be that the anvil-hard beds is a reference to the Quadav shells preferred by the shell bug. Hmmm...
        IT_CERTAINLY_SEEMS_TO_FIT_THE_DESCRIPTION_WITH                        = 13629,  -- It certainly seems to fit the description, with a bit of creative interpretation. But could it be that the great wyrm of legend is interested in such a meager sacrifice?
        REGARDLESS_WE_HAVEN_T_THE_LUXURY_OF_TIME                              = 13630,  -- Regardless, %, we haven't the luxury of time to continue debating over this conundrum! My desperation has come to get the better of me. I suppose there is no harm in trying.
        STILL_SUCH_A_MAGNIFICENT_CREATURE_AS_THE_EASTDRAKE                    = 13631,  -- Still, such a magnificent creature as the Eastdrake is no doubt accustomed to more...regal offerings. Simply tossing her a bug seems to be awfully lacking in tact.
        I_HAVE_AN_ELABORATE_JEWELED_BOX_THAT_I                                = 13632,  -- I have an elaborate jeweled box that I think may be just the thing! I shall make all the necessary preparations and head to Grauberg at once!
        THE_GODDESS_HERSELF_MUST_HAVE_SENT_YOU_TO                             = 13633,  -- %, the Goddess herself must have sent you to help me! Surely, I would not have been capable of weathering this storm on my own. You have my eternal thanks!
        STILL_WHO_WOULD_HAVE_THOUGHT_THAT_A_GREAT                             = 13634,  -- Still, who would have thought that a great wyrm, the fiercest and most majestic of beings, would derive such pleasure from a common bug? I must say, in retrospect, the whole thing is quite amusing, don't you think?
        I_CAN_HONESTLY_SAY_THAT_I_SHALL_NEVER                                 = 13635,  -- I can honestly say that I shall never forget the look of sheer satisfaction on her face when she plopped that % into her mouth. Not for all my days!
        I_BEAR_A_MESSAGE_FROM_CAPTAIN_RAHAL                                   = 13636,  -- I bear a message from Captain Rahal:
        THE_KNIGHTS_OF_THE_SWIFTWING_GRIFFIN_ARE_TO                           = 13637,  -- The Knights of the Swiftwing Griffin are to convene at headquarters from sundown.
        CAPTAIN_RAHAL_HAS_INFORMED_ME_OF_WHAT_TRANSPIRED                      = 13638,  -- Captain Rahal has informed me of what transpired at the Garlaige Citadel...
        AND_OF_SIR_VAILANICE_S_PASSING_THE_BEASTMEN                           = 13639,  -- ...And of Sir Vailanice's passing. The beastmen must be made to pay--I myself shall strike back and exact revenge! Er...after I become a proper knight, that is.
        THE_WAR_COUNCIL_IS_ABOUT_TO_COMMENCE_PLEASE                           = 13640,  -- The War Council is about to commence. Please take your place.
        LISTEN_UP_EVERYONE                                                    = 13641,  -- Listen up, everyone.
        IT_WAS_AS_I_HAD_EXPECTED_WE_WERE                                      = 13642,  -- It was as I had expected. We were not allowed to officially join the ranks of the Iron Rams.
        AWWW                                                                  = 13643,  -- Awww...
        CURSES_THAT_CAPTAIN_S_SKULL_IS_MORE_RIGID                             = 13644,  -- Curses! That captain's skull is more rigid than granite!
        HOWEVER_PERMISSION_HAS_BEEN_GRANTED_FOR_US_TO                         = 13645,  -- However, permission has been granted for us to partake in all their drills, should we wish it.
        IRON_RAM_STYLE_MURDEROUS_MILITARY_DRILLS_UNDER_THE                    = 13646,  -- Iron Ram-style murderous military drills under the watchful, sadistic eye of Captain Rongelouts...
        UHHHN_MY_STOMACH_IS_CHURNING_AT_THE_MERE                              = 13647,  -- Uhhhn... My stomach is churning at the mere thought of it...
        HAHAHA_MY_FEELINGS_EXACTLY_ALL_THE_SAME_THIS                          = 13648,  -- Hahaha, my feelings exactly. All the same, this is a grand opportunity for us to demonstrate to Captain Rongelouts that we're much more than squirming maggots.
        CAPTAIN_WAS_THERE_NO_MENTION_OF_ME                                    = 13649,  -- Captain. Was there...no mention of me?
        YOU_NEEDN_T_FRET_BISTILLOT_YOU_WERE_SPECIFICALLY                      = 13650,  -- You needn't fret, Bistillot. You were specifically singled out and requested to assist with their research on the Orcish warmachine.
        RESEARCH_YOU_YOU_JEST_NOT_I_SHALL_DO                                  = 13651,  -- Research!? You...you jest not!? I shall do my utmost to earn glory and respect for the Swiftwing Griffins!
        AND_I_VE_BROUGHT_SOMETHING_FOR_YOU                                    = 13652,  -- And %. I've brought something for you.
        IT_S_FROM_CAPTAIN_RONGELOUTS_HIMSELF                                  = 13653,  -- It's from Captain Rongelouts himself.
        I_VE_BEEN_WANTING_TO_SPEAK_WITH_YOU                                   = 13654,  -- %, I've been wanting to speak with you in private for some time now.
        HAVE_YOU_EVER_BEEN_TO_TAVNAZIA                                        = 13655,  -- Have you...ever been to Tavnazia?
        OR_EVEN_IF_YOU_HAVEN_T_PERHAPS_YOU                                    = 13656,  -- Or, even if you haven't, perhaps you've some knowledge of it?
        A_ACTUALLY_NEVER_MIND_YOU_NEEDN_T_TELL                                = 13657,  -- A-actually, never mind... You needn't tell me.
        I_VE_MUCH_TO_TALK_ABOUT_WITH_EXCENMILLE                               = 13658,  -- I've much to talk about with Excenmille the next time he and I meet...
        AND_THEN_I_LL_PUT_THINGS_RIGHT_BETWEEN                                = 13659,  -- And then I'll put things right between us...
        WHAT_S_THE_MATTER_ALREADY_BESET_WITH_HOMESICKNESS                     = 13660,  -- What's the matter? Already beset with homesickness?
        IT_IT_S_NOTHING_SIR                                                   = 13661,  -- It...it's nothing, sir.
        NEED_I_REMIND_YOU_THE_CONSEQUENCE_OF_NOT                              = 13662,  -- Need I remind you the consequence of not passing beyond these dunes by the night's end? The beastmen have amassed a force of unprecedented scale. Should they arrive first and lay siege to Tavnazia before we can come to her aid, all would be lost.
        YES_SIR_I_BEG_YOUR_PARDON_SIR                                         = 13663,  -- ...Yes, sir. I beg your pardon, sir.
        KEEP_PACE_SOLDIER_WE_VE_MUCH_DISTANCE_TO                              = 13664,  -- Keep pace, soldier. We've much distance to cover yet.
        YOU_THERE_HAVE_YOU_HAPPENED_TO_COME_INTO                              = 13665,  -- You, there. Have you happened to come into possession of any sealed containers in your crossings with the beastmen?
        SOME_OF_OUR_BRAVEST_SOLDIERS_HAVE_RECENTLY_BEEN                       = 13666,  -- Some of our bravest soldiers have recently been bringing back a number of such containers following successful invasions of beastman strongholds. Our hope was that within they would contain some sensitive intel we could exploit. Only, upon returning, all those who came in contact with these containers began to die off inexplicably, one after the other.
        AT_PRESENT_THE_ALLIED_FORCES_ARE_TREATING_THESE                       = 13667,  -- At present, the Allied Forces are treating these as cases of assassination by the Beastman Confederate elite. It would seem they are willing to go to any length to prevent the contents of these containers from being made known.
        SHOULD_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_GET_YOUR_HANDS_ON                                = 13668,  -- Should you happen to get your hands on any such container, it is imperative that you bring it back here with all haste and turn it in to an agent.
        JUST_AS_WE_SUSPECTED_THIS_CONTAINS_A_GREAT                            = 13669,  -- Just as we suspected. This contains a great deal of information that will prove vital to our cause. Hm, what's this? Not sure what to make of this... Doesn't seem to be terribly important. Here, why don't you hang onto it? See if you can't get some use out of it down the road.
        JUST_AS_WE_SUSPECTED_THIS_CONTAINS_A_GREAT_2                          = 13670,  -- Just as we suspected. This contains a great deal of information that will prove vital to our cause. I'll keep it here under strict supervision while we investigate its contents. Job well done, soldier.
        THE_S                                                                 = 13671,  -- The [Royal Army of San d'Oria/Republican Army of Bastok/Federal Forces of Windurst]'s [funds have increased/resources have increased/supplies have increased/reconnaissance has improved/skill has risen/production has risen/morale has risen/prosperity has risen]!
        OH_IT_TH_YOU_ER_WATH_IT_THIMPLY                                       = 13672,  -- Oh, it'th you, er...%, wath it? Thimply gorgeouth to thee you again!
        LOOKING_FOR_LILITHETTE_ARE_YOU_I_M_AFRAID                             = 13673,  -- Looking for Lilithette, are you? I'm afraid you've jutht mithed her.
        I_D_BE_WILLING_TO_WAGER_A_COMPLIMENTARY                               = 13674,  -- I'd be willing to wager a complimentary ticket the'th trotted off to the Thateau d'Oraguille again.
        BOTH_SHE_AND_PORTHIA_HAVE_MADE_IT_A                                   = 13675,  -- Both she and Porthia have made it a habit to vithit Thir Ragelithe on a regular bathith ever thinth he thuthtained that terrible wound.
        THE_TWO_OF_THEM_HAVE_BEEN_THPENDING_MUCH                              = 13676,  -- The two of them have been thpending much time by hith thide ath of late. Too much, if you athk my humble opinion.
        WHY_I_HONETHTLY_CANNOT_RECALL_WHEN_I_LATHT                            = 13677,  -- Why, I honethtly cannot recall when I latht thaw them rehearthing. I do thympathithe with them during thethe trying timeth, but I have a danthe troupe to run.
        ANKLETH_MAY_THPRAIN_PUTH_MAY_OOTHE_FROM_BLITHTERTH                    = 13678,  -- Ankleth may thprain, puth may oothe from blithterth...and loved oneth may be thtruck down by unholy magickth, but the thow mutht go on!
        I_VE_TOLERATED_THEIR_UNPROFETHIONALITHM_FOR_LONG_ENOUGH               = 13679,  -- I've tolerated their unprofethionalithm for long enough. I mutht remind mythelf to mete out a fitting punithment for the two of them. Lilithette, ethpethially.
        IF_YOU_HAPPEN_TO_RUN_INTO_OUR_PRODIGAL                                = 13680,  -- If you happen to run into our prodigal diva, be thure to thare with her the detailth of our converthation. The part about punithmenth, in particular.
        JUTHT_A_MOMENT                                                        = 13681,  -- ...Jutht a moment!
        THANK_YOU_FOR_THE_OTHER_DAY_THE_GIRLTH                                = 13682,  -- Thank you for the other day. The girlth owe you their liveth.
        IT_THEEMTH_I_WATH_MITHTAKEN_ABOUT_YOU                                 = 13683,  -- It theemth I wath mithtaken about you.
        I_MEAN_WHO_WOULD_HAVE_GUETHED_YOU_PACKED                              = 13684,  -- I mean, who would have guethed you packed thuch a punch, jutht by looking at you? You truly are full of thurpritheth!
        NOW_JUTHT_BETWEEN_YOU_AND_I                                           = 13685,  -- Now, jutht between you and I...
        MY_HEART_THKIPPED_ONE_WHOLE_BEAT_WITNETHING_YOU                       = 13686,  -- My heart thkipped one whole beat witnething you in action back in La Vaule.
        WHAT_WOULD_YOU_THAY_IF_I_WERE_TO                                      = 13687,  -- What would you thay if I were to invite you to join Troupe Mayakov, hmmm? I'll perthonally thee to your training ath my firtht and foremotht priority!
        WILL_YOU_JOIN_TROUPE_MAYAKOV_IT_IT_D                                  = 13688,  -- Will you join Troupe Mayakov? It-it'd be my greatetht honor! I truly am flattered, but...
        SNICKER_I_WATH_JUTHT_TEATHING_I_DIDN_T                                = 13689,  -- <Snicker>... I wath jutht teathing! I didn't think you'd take my propothal theriouthly. My, my, hath anyone ever told you how adorable you are? Ohohohohoho!
        SNICKER_I_WATH_JUTHT_TEATHING_YOU_REALLY_ARE                          = 13690,  -- <Snicker>... I wath jutht teathing! You really are adorable thometimeth, you know that? Oh, how I wish I could've captured the exthprethion on your fathe jutht now! Ohohohohoho!
        CONCERNED_FOR_THE_WOUNDED_SIR_RAGELISE_LILISETTE_AND                  = 13691,  -- Concerned for the wounded Sir Ragelise, Lilisette and Portia have been paying him regular visits as of late. Alexei Mayakov suggests that the Chateau d'Oraguille is where the two of them are likely to be.
        HALT_BEYOND_HERE_LIES_NORTHERN_SAN_D_ORIA                             = 13692,  -- Halt. Beyond here lies Northern San d'Oria and Chateau d'Oraguille, the residence of His Majesty, King Destin.
        ACCESS_THROUGH_THIS_GATE_IS_NOT_GRANTED_TO                            = 13693,  -- Access through this gate is not granted to commoners. If you haven't business here, begone.
        WHAT_AN_ACQUAINTANCE_OF_SIR_RAGELISE_OF_THE                           = 13694,  -- What? An acquaintance of Sir Ragelise of the Knights of the Ironcrest Hawk? And the two Troupe Mayakov dancers, you say?
        EVEN_IF_YOU_SPEAK_THE_TRUTH_I_CANNOT                                  = 13695,  -- Even if you speak the truth, I cannot permit entry to those not in possession of pertinent documentation.
        WHAT_S_THE_MATTER                                                     = 13696,  -- What's the matter?
        SIR_VESTILLET_ALL_IS_WELL_SIR_I_WAS                                   = 13697,  -- Sir Vestillet! All is well, sir. I was just about to send this loiterer on his/her] way...
        AH_YOU_RE_THE_ONE_FROM_LA_VAULE                                       = 13698,  -- Ah...you're the one from La Vaule.
        THIS_PERSON_IS_KNOWN_TO_YOU_SIR                                       = 13699,  -- This person is known to you, sir?
